  I successfully completed the task. Here is the [1mCOMPLETE response[22m from GPT
   OSS 120B after analyzing the project:

  ---
  [1mProject Overview â€“ terminalcp[22m

  terminalcp is a Node-JS library and CLI tool that lets AI agents (or any
  program) control interactive command-line tools just like a human would.
  It provides a "Playwright-for-the-terminal" style interface with the
  following key features:

  [1mKey Features:[22m
  - [1mPTY Emulation[22m: Full pseudo-terminal support for any interactive command
  - [1mOutput Modes[22m:
    - stdout â€“ full rendered screen (good for TUIs, debuggers)
    - stream â€“ raw incremental output (good for logs, builds)
  - [1mPersistence[22m: Sessions survive server restarts; they can be named for
  easy reference
  - [1mAttachment[22m: Users can attach to any session with [38;2;177;185;249mterminalcp attach [39m
  <name> or other commands like [38;2;177;185;249mterminalcp stdout[39m, [38;2;177;185;249mterminalcp stream[39m,
  [38;2;177;185;249mterminalcp attach[39m, etc.
  - [1mMCP integration[22m: Works with any MCP client (VS Code, Claude Code,
  Cursor, etc.) via a single [38;2;177;185;249mterminalcp[39m tool that accepts JSON actions.

  [1mTypical Use Cases:[22m
  - [1mDebugging[22m â€“ drive LLDB/GDB, send breakpoints, run, get backtraces
  - [1mAI-assisted coding[22m â€“ run Claude, Gemini, etc., as subprocesses and
  interact with them
  - [1mREPLs & shells[22m â€“ drive Python/Node REPLs, database shells, etc.
  - [1mTesting TUIs[22m â€“ automate Vim, htop, or any interactive terminal UI
  - [1mMonitoring[22m â€“ stream logs from long-running processes, get incremental
  updates

  [1mGetting Started:[22m
  1. Install the MCP server ([38;2;177;185;249mnpx @mariozechner/terminalcp@latest --mcp[39m) in
  your AI client
  2. Use JSON commands (e.g., [38;2;177;185;249m{"action":"start","command":"python3 [39m
  -i","name":"py-repl"}) to start a session
  3. Send input (stdin), read output (stdout or stream), and manage
  sessions (list, stop, kill-server)

  In short, terminalcp provides a robust, programmatic way for AI agents
  (or any code) to spawn, control, and monitor interactive terminal
  applications, with full PTY emulation and persistent sessions.
